<div><span class="gmail_quote">On 11/28/07, <b class="gmail_sendername">George Bosilca</b> &lt;<a href="mailto:bosilca@eecs.utk.edu">bosilca@eecs.utk.edu</a>&gt; wrote:</span>
<blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="PADDING-LEFT: 1ex; MARGIN: 0px 0px 0px 0.8ex; BORDER-LEFT: #ccc 1px solid">If your F77 compiler do not support array of LOGICAL variables (which<br>seems to be the case if you look in the 
config.log file), then you&#39;re<br>left with only one option. Remove the F77 support from the<br>compilation. This means adding the --disable-mpi-f77 option to the ./<br>configure.<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Thanks,<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;george.<br><br>
